author: COMSOL
description: This tutorial models lithium plating and dendrite growth in a lithium-ion battery. Pulse reverse plating is used to attenuate small protrusions during lithium metal deposition. By matching the process parameters, including the length of the forward and reverse pulses (duty cycles), spikes of lithium dendrites can be avoided.
